post_text:
Instructions for students and patrons who are planning on going to the middle school volleyball game at Yates Center on Thursday.

Spectators:
We recommend that all spectators wear masks while in the gym, at the concession stand and bathrooms.
Admission will be free at Middle School games.
Contactless temperature checks will be performed for all spectators as they enter the building. Spectators with a temperature above 100 degrees will be asked to return home.
Social distancing where possible, we encourage families to sit in clusters and leave distance between families.
Parents please keep small children with you to ensure their safety.
Frequent hand washing or sanitizing
We encourage you to stay home if you are not feeling well or have been in contact with someone who is not feeling well.

post_text:
On September 3, the MS Lady Jet volleyball team will be traveling to Yates Center to play a duel. Only the "A" team will play Thursday. 5:00 PM start.

On September 4, the AMHS football team will be taking on Marmaton Valley at home on Frank Kennedy Field beginning at 7:00 PM. Parent's/Sr. Night will begin at 6:40 followed by the football game. Football, Volleyball, Cheer and Band seniors and their parents will be recognized. We ask everyone wear a mask around the concession stand. Other than that, a mask is optional. Admission will be $4.00/adult $2.00 for students. Car loads of 3 or more will be charged $10. There will not be any programs. However, there will be a sheet about parents night as you get to the bleachers. You may bring lawn chairs to help with social distancing. You will not be allowed to sit on the track. Go Jets!

post_text: This young man, Conner Houghton, represented the AM Jets at Kansas Wesleyan University the last few days with such class and respect to all teammates & coaches. He is to be commended not only for his representation but also for all the awards he received! "Most improved EVERY session" among others shown. There were only 2 kids at the camp who received 5 stars (the highest ranking) and one of them was Conner for "Most Coachable." We are BEYOND proud!! WAY TO GO CONNER!!!!!

post_text: Physical forms for the 20-21 school year will be passed out at Sports Camps beginning Friday 7/17, through the next week. Food service will also have the forms available Monday when they deliver meals. Please ask for these forms at they time of your food pick-up. The forms will be available in the district office beginning Monday, 7/20. If you need forms mailed, please call the district office at 620-537-7721. The physicals will be given in Neodesha on Aug. 10 & 11. Transportation will be available from the high school and the elementary school. Times will be confirmed and we will get that information out to you ASAP. It is always an option and advised, to see your family doctor or the free clinic in Altoona. The free clinic only open on Wednesdays. You must have the form completed before you will be seen. Questions?? E-mail jalmond@usd387.org

2019-2020 GRADUATION ANNOUNCEMENT
The 2019-2020 Altoona-Midway High School Graduation will take place on July 18, 2020, at
3:00pm. The ceremony will be held in the Milo E. Peterson Gymnasium. ALL family and friends
are welcome to attend. HOWEVER, everyone in attendance will be required to wear a mask.
This is not an option. Anyone refusing to wear a mask will not be allowed in the building. This
precaution is for the well-being of our students and all others in attendance.
We appreciate your cooperation. Please join us as we celebrate the class of 2020.

post_text: Prom and Graduation Announcement: After discussions with and recommendations from the Wilson County Health Department, prom will be canceled for July 11. This was not an easy decision but one that must be made. As of this notice, graduation will proceed as planned on July 18. More details will be released as the information becomes available. Please continue to monitor our social medial outlets, as that is where the most up-to-date information will be.

post_text: Sports Camp Announcement- After discussions with and recommendations from the Wilson County Health Department, sports camps will go on as planned starting July 6. Sports camps participants will not be required to wear masks. Social distancing will be practiced with very little contact. We will have individual water bottles for each camper and they will be sanitized daily at the school. Coaches will discuss further precautions at the beginning of camp. Please continue to monitor our social medial outlets, as that is where the most up-to-date information will be.

post_text: Summer Academy Announcement- After discussions with and recommendations from the Wilson county Health Department, Summer Academy will go on as planned starting July 6. Masks will be provided. For 1st grade and up. Busses will be disinfected daily. No masks will be required if the bus windows are down so transportation will be provided as scheduled. We will have individual water bottles for each student and they will be sanitized daily at the school. Friday field trips have been canceled but the Summer Academy will be continuing on Fridays. There will be more information coming out to our social media outlets July 3. Thanks for your patience and understanding as we keep the safety of our kids first and foremost in our minds. Please continue to monitor our social medial outlets, as that is where the most up-to-date information will be.

post_text: Important announcement concerning summer activities: We are waiting to hear from Destiny Wheeler from The Wilson County Health Department to call back with the protocols for our Summer activities. These activities include Summer Academy, sports camps, prom and graduation. I know we are all hoping to offer our kids these opportunities, but we have to follow whatever guidelines the county has in place. Hopefully, we will know something for sure tomorrow. Thank you for your patience and we will get the word out as quickly as possible through our social media outlets.

post_text:
Senior Citizen Meals

We have received a grant that will allow us to serve meals to the Senior Citizens of the Altoona Community! We will be serving the same sack meals as we do for the students. There will be 5 breakfasts and 5 lunches with pick up on Mondays from 9a.m.-10a.m. at the Elementary through the month of July. If you are a person 50 or older in the Altoona area and would like to pick up meals or have questions please contact me at 785-383-1835 or dcook@usd387.org.
We have also made a donation from the grant to the Senior Citizens of Buffalo Organization to support their monthly meal program.

Diane

July Meals

If you are not currently picking up meals, but would like to, please contact me at 785-383-1835 or dcook@usd387.org. If you are currently picking up meals, I will keep you on the list. Please let me know if you would like to stop.

Diane

Altoona-Midway FFA
May 9 at 8:10 AM ·

#FFAFriday (better late than never again) this week highlights our proficiency award winners at the chapter level. Proficiency awards are for those who have projects outside of the classroom (aka Supervised Agricultural Experience or SAE) related to agriculture and have financial records related to said project.

*Abigale Reaves- Vet Science Placement (also placed 2nd in Southeast District!) & Diversified Livestock Production
*Josie Huffman- Food Science Placement
*Joshua Meigs- Turf Grass Management
*Caden Berger- Ag Mechanics Placement
*Jada Davis- Poultry & Rabbit Production
*Emma Martin- Creed Speaking & Ag Production Placement

*Also, our Chapter Star Farmer this year is Abigale Reaves. Our Chapter Star Greenhand is Emma Martin.

Congratulations to all members on your hardwork and another successful year 👏

post_text:
Hello, everyone. As we are coming to the end of another school year, I want to say how much I enjoyed your children. I know these last few weeks have been especially crazy. I am incredibly proud of all of our students, parents/guardians, and staff who worked so hard and so well to take care of business.

I am sad that we did not get to go through these last two months with our seniors. They are a great group of young people, and they will forever be “my kids”. However, I am looking forward to next year. I cannot wait to see our kids again. I believe we will come out of all this even stronger and have a great year.

Again, I want to say thank you for everything. I hope everyone has a great summer and remains healthy and happy.

Sincerely,
Darrin Ashmore
Principal

post_text: We will collect all of the student devices on May 13th and 14th. You can drop the devices off at either AMES or the High School/Middle School. It does not make any difference which building your student attends, you can drop off at either location. Drop off times will be from 8:30 to 3:30. We will have personnel located outside or directly in the lobby areas, depending on weather. When you drop off the device, please verify with the school personnel that it was credited to the correct student(s). If neither of these days and times work for you, please contact the elementary or the high school office to schedule a different time. Please ensure that you bring the devices, chargers, and cases.
